<main>
<!-- ============ FEATURES ============ -->
<section class="features" id="features">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Features</span>
      <h2>Everything a Blazor team needs to ship dashboards fast</h2>
      <p>A focused toolset for real interfaces — not another toy demo generator.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-grid reveal">
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 3v3M12 18v3M4.2 4.2l2.1 2.1M17.7 17.7l2.1 2.1M3 12h3M18 12h3M4.2 19.8l2.1-2.1M17.7 6.3l2.1-2.1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3.4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Prompt-to-Dashboard</h3>
        <p>Describe the dashboard you want in plain English. Bilboard plans the layout and writes the BIL structure — ready to edit, export, or drop straight into your app.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><rect x="3.5" y="3.5" width="7" height="7" rx="1.6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/><rect x="13.5" y="3.5" width="7" height="7" rx="1.6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/><rect x="3.5" y="13.5" width="7" height="7" rx="1.6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/><rect x="13.5" y="13.5" width="7" height="7" rx="1.6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Native BIL Components</h3>
        <p>Every output is composed of real BIL primitives — charts, tables, cards, layouts — so it reads like markup your own team would have written.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="5" cy="6" r="2.3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/><circle cx="19" cy="6" r="2.3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/><circle cx="12" cy="18" r="2.3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/><path d="M6.8 7.7L11 16M17.2 7.7L13 16" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Agentic Workflow</h3>
        <p>Specialized agents plan, compose, and validate each dashboard step by step, instead of guessing the whole thing in a single brittle pass.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M4 12l6-8v5h10l-6 8v-5H4z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Token-Efficient Output</h3>
        <p>A compact intermediate JSON representation means Bilboard ships the same dashboard using 2.8× fewer tokens than Claude.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M8 6l-5 6 5 6M16 6l5 6-5 6M13.5 4l-3 16" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Developer-Grade Markup</h3>
        <p>Clean Razor output, predictable naming, typed bindings, and component boundaries that match the conventions your team already uses.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M13 2L4 14h6l-1 8 9-12h-6l1-8z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></div>
