        <button class="faq-q"><span>What is Bilboard?</span><span class="plus"></span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>Bilboard is an agentic AI platform that turns natural-language prompts into production-ready Blazor dashboards, built on top of BIL (Blazor Interface Library).</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q"><span>Is it only for Blazor?</span><span class="plus"></span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes — Bilboard is purpose-built for Blazor and outputs native BIL components. That focus is what enables higher quality and lower token usage than general-purpose models.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q"><span>Does it use BIL components?</span><span class="plus"></span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>Every generated dashboard is composed entirely of BIL primitives, so the output looks and behaves like code your team would write by hand.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q"><span>How is it different from Claude?</span><span class="plus"></span></button>
